race to nowhere screening & town hall education and society theme house race to nowhere screening & town hall submitted by kevinmorton on mon 10 17 2011 22 51 race to nowhere is a provocative new documentary challenging prevailing views of how to foster high school student success it is a fascinating expose of student stress cheating lack of motivation and inefficient student outcomes we envision ourselves at east as stanford's hub for education related programming and debate and we could not pass up the chance to show the movie accompanied with a spirited discussion as our kickoff event rsvp for the screening rsvp for the town hall meeting we would love to see you at both events but please attend what fits best in your schedule we will be serving our delicious coho catering before the town meeting around 8 00 pm hope this helps for meal planning discussion moderated by professor christine min wotipka stanford school of education panel participants include vicki abeles director of race to nowhere sheila altmann school psychologist at monta vista high school bob patterson stanford director of undergraduate admissions daniel wong stanford class of 2013 login to post comments home welcome we are the education and society theme east house directions here we seek to establish the salience of education and the relationship between education and society on stanford campus through outreach to undergraduates and residential based programming please contact us with any comments or suggestions new forum topics photographs for waiting for superman more user login username password request new password education and society theme house calendar of events programs at east living at east bulletin board about us contact us visit the education theme house at 544 governor's avenue between lagunita and frosoco drupal theme designed by blamcast
